        <comment>This node represents the thioredoxin cytosolic pool, an important element on the antioxidant machinery of the cell. It receives electrons from NADPH and transfers the electrons to other signaling proteins [2]. In some cases of reductive stress the extremely reduced TRX pool is an inductor of ROS production by the enzyme Thioredoxin Reductase [3]. It is a multilevel node.

Level 2 --&gt; highly reduced
Level 1 --&gt; normal physiological reduction status
Level 0 --&gt; highly oxidized</comment>
